summary:
Former Olympic rower, investment banker, venture capitalist and entrepreneur, now having started my own new-style venture capital firm "No Such Ventures", DIFFERENTIATING itself from most other investors:

- we are NO OLD SCHOOL FUND, funded by passive fund investors ü•± , BUT INVEST deal-by-deal, 
BACKED BY an engaged and capable group of ACTIVE ENTREPRENEURS and SENIOR MANAGERS, 
who have active business networks üåê , which can be used for business leads, potential hirings and what not

- deal-by-deal investing ensures FLEXIBILITY ü§∏‚Äç‚ôÄÔ∏è in terms of 1. investing in new shares and existing shares 2. % stake 3. (exit) timelines 4. follow-ons, 5. geo, 6. sector, etc., as we don't have a strict fund mandate

- we INVEST IN FEWER COMPANIES üí™ , which makes sure we invest with conviction and WITH MORE RESOURCES and future funding for these companies, instead of using the common 'spray-and-pray' üí¶ tactic, investing in a large number of companies

Long story short: we invest ‚Ç¨2m - ‚Ç¨8m in ambitious companies
